view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you specify is a descendant of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIControl"},{"type":"text","text":" class, the map view calls this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method as a convenience whenever the user taps your view. You can use this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method to respond to taps and perform any actions associated with that control."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, if your control displays additional information about the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotation, you could use this method to present a modal panel with that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your custom accessory views are not descendants of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIControl"},{"type":"text","text":" class,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the map view does not call this method. If the annotation has a custom callout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"view via the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-mapView:calloutViewForAnnotation:"},{"text":" method, you can specify the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"custom accessory views using the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCalloutView","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"leftAccessoryView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rightAccessoryView"},{"text":" properties.","type":"text"}]},{"level":4,"text":"Related examples","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Default callout usage, learn how to trigger an action when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"standard callout bubb